This paper deals with decision-making under uncertainty and resource allocation, which are topics that are commonly studied in game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves optimization and algorithm design, which are relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) category. Finally, the paper discusses the social implications of resource allocation, which could fall under the computer and society (cs.CY) category.
